By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – The Senate on Tuesday announced 69 committees it will rely upon to execute its legislative duties in the 9th Assembly. The President of the Senate, Ahmed Lawan made the announcement at the close of plenary on Tuesday. The Senate thereafter adjourned sitting to 24 of September 2019 to observe its annual break. Below are the full list of Chairmen and Vice Chairman of Senate Committees. 1. AGRICULTURE AND RURAL DEVELOPMENTSen Abdullah I AdamuSen Birma Mohammed 2. AIRFORCESenators Bala Ibn N’AllahSen. Michael Nnachi 3. ANTI-CORRUPTION AND FINANCIAL CRIMESSen. Suleiman AbdulkwariSen. Magatakarda Wamako 4. APPROPRIATIONSSen Ibrahim Barau JibrinSen Stella Adaeze Odua 5. ARMYSen Ali NdumeSen. Abba Moro 6. AVIATIONSen. Dino MelayeSenator Bala N’Allah 7. BANKING INSURANCE AND OTHER FINANCIAL INSTITUTIONSSen. Ubansu SaniSen Orji’s Uzor Kalu 8. CAPITAL MARKETSen Ibikunle AmosunSen Buenos Dauda 9. COMMUNICATIONSSen. Oluremi TinubuSen Ibrahim Mohammed Bomai 10. COOPERATION AND INTEGRATION IN AFRICA AND NEPADSen Chimaroke NnamaniSen Yusuf Abubakar Yusuf 11. CULTURE AND TOURISMSen Rochas OkorochaSen Ignatius Longjam 13. CUSTOMS EXCISE AND TARIFFSen Francis AlimikhenaSen Francis Fadausi 14. DEFENCESen Magatakarda WamakkoSen. Istifanus Dung Gyang 15. DIASPORA AND NGOsSen SurajudeenSen Yahaya Ibrahim Lawal 16. DOWNSTREAM PETROLEUM SECTORSen Sabo Muhammed NakuduSen. Philip Aduda 17. DRUGS AND NARCOTICSSen Ezekiel Ayuba DimkaSen. Chimaroke Nnamani 18. ECOLOGY AND CLIMATE CHANGESen Hassan GusauSen Olubunmi Adetumbi 19. EDUCATION, BASIC AND SECONDARYSen Ibrahim GeidamSen Okon Etim 20. EMPLOYMENT LABOUR AND PRODUCTIVITYSen. Benjamin UwajumoguSen. Kabiru Barkiya 21. ENVIRONMENTSen Ike EkweremaduSen Ibrahim Hassan Hadeja 22. ESTABLISHMENT AND PUBLIC SERVICESen Ibrahim ShekarauSen Barinada Ndigi 23. ETHICS AND PRIVILEGES AND PUBLIC PETITIONSSen Patrick Ayo AkinyelureAhmad Baba Keita 24. FCTSen Abubakar Shuaibu KyariSen Tolu Odeniyi 25. FEDERAL CHARACTER AND INTERGOVERNMENTAL AFFAIRSSen Danjuma TalaSen Lawal Yahaya Gumau 26. FERMASen Gershon Henry BasseySen Abdulkadir Kabiru Barkiya 27. FINANCESen Adeola Solomon OlamilekanSen Isa Jibril 28. FOREIGN AFFAIRSSen Isa BulkachuwaSen Ignatius Longjam 29. GAS RESOURCESSen James ManagerSen Biobarakuma Degi Eremenyo 30. HEALTH SECONDARY AND TERTIARYSen. Ibrahim OloriegbeSen Betty Apiafi 31. HOUSINGSen Samuel EgwuSen Lola Isa Hashiru 32. ICT AND CYBER CRIMESSen Yakubu HussainiSen Abdulfatah Buhari 33. INECSen Kabiru GayaSen Sahab Alhaji-Yau 34. INDUSTRIESSen Sikiru OshinowoSen Saidu Alkali 35. INFORMATION AND NATIONAL ORIENTATIONSen Abdullah SankaraSen Aishatu Dahiru Ahmed 36. INTERIORSen Kassim ShettimaSen Siri Duoye 37. INTER-PARLIAMENTARY AFFAIRSSen Akwashiki GodiyaSen Abba Moro 38. JUDICIARY AND LEGAL MATTERSSen Michael BamideleSen Emmanuel Orke-jev 39. LAND TRANSPORTSen Abdulfatah BuhariSen Nicholas Tofowomo 40. LEGISLATIVE COMPLIANCESen Orielowo AdeyemiSen Sabina Abdullahi 41. LOCAL CONTENTSen Senator Teslim FolarinSen Aliyu. Sabi Abdullahi 42. LOCAL AND FOREIGN DEBTSen Clifford OrdiaSen Birma Mohammed Elagi 43. MARINE TRANSPORTATIONSen Danjuma GojeSen Sikiru Adebayo Oshonowo 44. MEDIA AND PUBLIC AFFAIRSSen Clement Adedayo AdeyeyeSen Akwashiki Godiya 45. NATIONAL IDENTITY AND POPULATIONSen Olubunmi AdetumbiSen Lawrence Ehrwudjakpor 46. NATIONAL SECURITY AND INTELLIGENCESen Ibrahim Abdullah GobirSen Chukwuka Utazi 47. NAVYSenator George SekiboSen Elisha Clifford Abbi 48. NIGER DELTASenator Peter NwuabushiSenator Bulus Amos 49. PETROLEUM RESOURCES UPSTREAMSenator Albert Bassey AkpanPatrick Ifeanyi Uba 50. POLICE AFFAIRSSenator Dauda Hakuri JikaSenator Abubakar Tambuwal 51. POVERTY ALLEVIATION AND SOCIAL INVESTMENT PROGRAMMESenator Lawal Yahaya GumauSenator Michael Nnachi 52. POWERSen. Gabriel SuswanSen. Eyinnaya Abaribe 53. PRIMARY HEALTHCARE AND COMMUNICABLE DISEASESSenator. Chukwuka UtaziSen Sadiq Suleiman Umar 54. PRIVATISATIONSen Theodore OrjiSen Oriolowo Adeyemi 